ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: As I said before, definitely NOT recommended unless there is huge change and the professor is committed to devote much more time into this course.

Definitely consider it. The lectures are dull, but the project can be a really rewarding experience if you have reliable, dedicated team members. I did, and it was tons of fun. Make sure you group chooses an idea you all really can get around, starts early, and works on a consistent schedule.

This is a very good software engineering course. You will have the chance to experience what software engineering is like in industry in working with other classmates. It is a good practice before you set your career path as a software engineer.
Yes, a great course training your coding ability.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I plan to be a software engineer after graduation. During this course, i have been exposed to core concepts of software engineering and had hands on practice of developing a software with a team.
deepen the skill in practical programming
